  <act:title>Fraudulent Conveyance Act</act:title>
  <act:chapter>163</act:chapter>
  <act:yearenacted>1996</act:yearenacted>
  <act:currency>
    <act:tlcDirPath>1198514681/96163/1059570960</act:tlcDirPath>
    <act:tlc>E2tlc96163</act:tlc>
  </act:currency>
  <act:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e15">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Fraudulent conveyance to avoid debt or duty of others</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>If made to delay, hinder or defraud creditors and others of their just and lawful remedies</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e26">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>a disposition of property, by writing or otherwise,</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e35">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>a bond,</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e45">
        <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>a proceeding, or</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e54">
        <bcl:num>d</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>an order</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:text>is void and of no effect against a person or the person's assignee or personal representative whose rights and obligations are or might be disturbed, hindered, delayed or defrauded, despite a pretence or other matter to the contrary.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e67">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Application of Act</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>This Act does not apply to a disposition of property for good consideration and in good faith lawfully transferred to a person who, at the time of the transfer, has no notice or knowledge of collusion or fraud.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
  </act:content>
